# Project documentation (authoritative)

Before designing features, APIs, data models, or folder structure for this repo, align with the documents under `docs/`:

1. **`docs/product-requirements.md`** — What the system must do (behavior, use cases, data model, phases A1–A4).
2. **`docs/engineering-requirements.md`** — How to implement it (structure, APIs, in-memory vs DB, validation).
3. **`docs/PROJECT-GUIDE.md`** — How those two relate, assignment alignment, and consistency rules.

When the user’s task touches scope, requirements, or architecture, read the relevant sections from these files (or ask to include them) instead of guessing. Prefer small changes that match the documented phase and avoid scope creep beyond the PRD/engineering doc.
